{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3565530,"name":"Carl Hauser","username":"chauser","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/a587f6/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-22T20:39:56.488Z","cooked":"<p>We saw our autos at competition pause briefly about 1.5 seconds into the auto. We eventually determined that this was correlated with a scheduler loop overrun (40-100ms) occurring in our SwerveSubsystem.periodic() method. From the timing we suspected that it occurred when the the cameras first identified an Apriltag. We subsequently confirmed this at home: with the robot sitting idle after restarting robot code, revealing an Apriltag in the camera field of view causes a loop overrun in SwerveSubsystem.periodic(). Subsequently hiding and revealing the Apriltag does not cause further occurrences.</p>
<p>The code of SwerveSubsystem.periodic() is</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public void periodic()
{
    // When vision is enabled we must manually update odometry in SwerveDrive
    if (visionDriveTest)
    {
      m_LeftEstimatedPose = CameraSubsystem.getGlobalPoseFromLeft();
      m_RightEstimatedPose = CameraSubsystem.getGlobalPoseFromRight();
      if (m_LeftEstimatedPose.isPresent()) {
        swerveDrive.addVisionMeasurement(m_LeftEstimatedPose.get().estimatedPose.toPose2d(), m_LeftEstimatedPose.get().timestampSeconds);
      }
      if (m_RightEstimatedPose.isPresent()) {
        swerveDrive.addVisionMeasurement(m_RightEstimatedPose.get().estimatedPose.toPose2d(), m_RightEstimatedPose.get().timestampSeconds);
      }
      if (m_LeftEstimatedPose.isPresent( )&amp;&amp; m_RightEstimatedPose.isPresent()) {
      SmartDashboard.putString("Pose Difference", m_LeftEstimatedPose.get().estimatedPose.toPose2d()
                                                      .minus(m_RightEstimatedPose.get().estimatedPose.toPose2d()).toString());
      }
      swerveDrive.updateOdometry();
//      vision.updatePoseEstimation(swerveDrive);
    }
  }
</code></pre>
<p><code>visionDriveTest</code> is <code>true</code>.</p>
<p>We have subsequently added timing measurements between each of the statements in this code and determined that the big time-takers are one of the <code>CameraSubsystem.getGlobalPoseFrom*();</code>  (Whichever sees the tag first). and the call to <code>swerveDrive.addVisionMeasurement</code> which is just a wrapper for WPILib’s PoseEstimator.addVisionMeasurement. The <code>CameraSubsystem.getGlobalPoseFrom*();</code> methods look like:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">    public static Optional&lt;EstimatedRobotPose&gt; getGlobalPoseFromLeft() {            
        Optional&lt;EstimatedRobotPose&gt; result = Optional.empty();
        if(m_photonPoseEstimatorLeft != null){
            result = m_photonPoseEstimatorLeft.update(m_LeftCam.getLatestResult());
            return result;
        }
        return result;
    }
</code></pre>
<p>where it appears the line <code>result = m_photonPoseEstimatorLeft.update(m_LeftCam.getLatestResult());</code> is the likely culprit. But why this would take a long time on the first result that actually sees a tag and not later ones is a mystery.</p>
<p>Does anybody have any insight as to what is happening here? or what to do to fix or mitigate it?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2025-03-22T20:39:56.488Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":180,"readers_count":179,"score":71.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":496550,"topic_slug":"loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag","display_username":"Carl Hauser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36833,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag/496550/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3565545,"name":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/slab-mr.thomas/{size}/182153_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-22T21:41:11.253Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="chauser" data-post="1" data-topic="496550">
