<p>Regardless of the strategy there is only a single tag in view of the camera when this happens.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2025-03-23T04:57:13.327Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":121,"readers_count":120,"score":24.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":496550,"topic_slug":"loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag","display_username":"Carl Hauser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":65,"username":"Joe_Ross","name":"Joe Ross","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joe_ross/{size}/37_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36833,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag/496550/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3565849,"name":"Carl Hauser","username":"chauser","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/a587f6/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-23T05:02:15.700Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks. I dont think that’s directly it – we have only one WPILib pose estimator – but it is interesting that having two could cause the same symptom. Something to keep in mind as we dig in further.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2025-03-23T05:02:15.700Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":112,"readers_count":111,"score":22.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":496550,"topic_slug":"loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag","display_username":"Carl Hauser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":24594,"username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","name":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/slab-mr.thomas/{size}/182153_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36833,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag/496550/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3565850,"name":"guineawheek","username":"guineawheek","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/guineawheek/{size}/180797_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-23T05:12:13.130Z","cooked":"<p>We’ve been having similar issues as well and we suspect the issue relates to how Java classes are lazy-loaded; the first time code paths get run on robot restart, Java needs to actually load the classes in and run them. We’ve been waving apriltags in front of our robot before setting it on the starting position in matches for this reason</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2025-03-23T05:12:13.130Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":99,"readers_count":98,"score":69.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":496550,"topic_slug":"loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag","display_username":"guineawheek","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":31855,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"software @ redux robotics"},"post_url":"/t/loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag/496550/6","custom_user_title":"software @ redux robotics","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":3}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":3,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3565858,"name":"Carl Hauser","username":"chauser","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/a587f6/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-23T05:29:59.777Z","cooked":"<p>Delayed code loading was one of the hypotheses that we were considering and trying to figure out how to test.</p>
<p>We had thought about “wave a tag” as a mitigation and have resisted out of concern that showing the wrong tag would cause the robot to believe it was in the wrong place on the field, potentially causing it to do something highly inappropriate for the real location once enabled. Do you have a code solution for this or are you just really careful about what tag you show?</p>
<p>One thing I’m thinking of trying tomorrow is generating a dummy, but valid (not quite sure what that entails) PhotonPipeLineResult and feeding it to the PhotonPoseEstimators immediately after they are constructed. That should force any code loading that needs to happen. By not ever passing the results to the WPILib PoseEstimator I think that the robot will not be confused about its location. Oh ho! That suggests that it may be ok if we don’t feed the PhotonPoseEstimator results to the WPILib PoseEstimator when the robot is disabled – that would be easy to accomplish.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2025-03-23T05:29:59.777Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":93,"readers_count":92,"score":28.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":496550,"topic_slug":"loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag","display_username":"Carl Hauser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":31855,"username":"guineawheek","name":"guineawheek","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/guineawheek/{size}/180797_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36833,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/loop-overrun-when-photonvision-sees-first-apriltag/496550/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3565863,"name":"guineawheek","username":"guineawheek","avatar_template":"/u